Case Analysis

Linear Search:

Best Case: Target is at the first index → Only 1 comparison → O(1).

Worst Case: Target is at the last index or not present → All 30 comparisons → O(n).

Average Case: Target is somewhere in the middle → About n/2 comparisons → O(n).

Binary Search:

Best Case: Target is at the middle in the first comparison → O(1).

Worst Case: Target requires repeatedly dividing until 1 element left → O(log n).

Average Case: On average, about log₂(n) comparisons → O(log n).
